02/12/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Tourism Minister Dimitris Avramopoulos visited Ankara on Wednesday (1 December) at the invitation of Turkish counterpart Erkan Mumcu. 
Stressing that both countries must learn to better appreciate and respect each other, Avramopoulos said the visit aimed to further boost bilateral relations. 
He added that an agreement on co-operation in the field of tourism would be signed next year. 
(ANA, MPA - 01/12/04)
